<td colspan=3 class=black><br><p><font class=b>Objective</font><br><font class=black>
This is the classic most recognized game of solitaire.  Turn 3 cards at a time, and go through the deck as many times as you like. The game will start with 0 points. You get 5 points for each card moved on to the piles, 1 point for moving a card from the deck to the play area, and 100 points for finishing the game.<br><br>
To build your stacks, you may either draw a card from the "draw pile" or move an existing stack of cards. The cards must be alternate colors and the numbers must descend in order. The main objective is to clear the board of cards by organizing them, in ascending order, into four suits at the upper right. When you can add a card to the suit stack click once and drag the card to the location you wish to place it. To place a card or move a stack around on the board click and drag the cards.<br>










































































































































































































































































































